textAfterTable: 88878 Bowenyueli           Discovered 2001 Sept. 25 by W. K. Y. Yeung at the Desert Eagle Observatory. The motto of the Chinese University of Hong Kong is bowenyueli, which means "Through learning and temperance to virtue". These words of Confucius have long been considered a principal precept of his teaching. The University lays equal emphasis on the intellectual and moral aspects of education.
